Condonement allows students to progress without reassessment for failed modules if overall performance is good.  
Steps:   
1. Meet program-specific condonement criteria;  
2. No need for resits or repeats in condoned modules;  
3. Progress treated as passed, affecting qualification positively.  
Source: Chapter 4, Section 6.3 of UCL Academic Manual

Student Quality Reviewers analyze education areas from a student perspective.  
1. Join as an Internal Quality Reviewer or Programme/Assessment Design Partner;  
2. Engage with staff in ChangeMakers Teaching Dialogue scheme for teaching reflection;  
3. Advocate diverse perspectives through Student Curriculum Partner role; ✅ Pay a stipend of £300 for around 25 hours work. Source: Information on module feedback and student involvement roles in the UCL CS Handbook.
